Topology of DHCP

When you are configuring 1 router, 1 server, 3 pcs, to 1 switch " sometimes you may come accross as "connection error: "the cable cannot be connected to the port" ".

then go to switch and open it by double clicking on it.

the go to physical

then turn off the switch

then to the right buttom corner you will find ports drag it and drop it to one of the empty slots

then turn on the switch

then try connecting the rest of the devices to switch

if you are getting the same error then try performing the same steps again.
